  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Livelihood Enhancement for Farm Families (LEFF) in Port Loko District</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Farmer households, Women, Youth</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Placement of animals, training in Cornerstones, Leadership, Crop and Livestock Integration, Animal Wellbeing, Provision of seeds (Rice &amp;amp; Groundnut), Veterinary Support, Exchange Visits, Sensitization HIV/AIDs, Water and Sanitation and the Environment, influencing policies, systems and practices</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal of the project is to improve the livelihood of 1,100 beneficiaries (567 women and 533 men) in the Port Loko District of Sierra Leone. The selected beneficiaries of this project are handicapped by limited resources, poor nutrition, high youth unemployment, environmental degradation and low capacities of community structures to lead development initiative. The objectives of Livelihood Enhancement for Farm Families (LEFF) are : 1) to increase income generation  
2) improve nutrition of  rural families by establishing seed banks  
3) promote sound environmental practices including zero grazing, aforestation, use of organic fertilizers and 
4) conduct training and sensitization in project management, group organization, gender equity and HIV/AIDS in  six (6) Chiefdoms namely Maforki, Tainkatopa Makama Safroko (TMS), Marampa, Buya Romende, Koya and Masimera in Port Loko district.</narrative>
  </description>
